==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*bidja-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[bidda]], Old Saxon [[biddian]] (Dutch [[bidden]]), Old High German [[bitten]] (German [[bitten]]), Old Norse [[biðja]] (Swedish [[bedja]]), Gothic [[𐌱𐌹𐌳𐌾𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'bɪddan/

===Verb===
'''biddan''' (class V strong)
# to ask for, to [[entreat]] or [[beg]], to [[demand]]
#:''He bæd him hlafas wyrcan'': he bade him make loaves of bread.  (Cædmon's ''Metrical Paraphrase'')

